<item>
            <title>[LU-138] liblustreapi fails to link using --no-add-needed linkerflags</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-138</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;lustre currently fails to build using binutils-gold or by simply adding --no-add-needed to the linker flags. &lt;br/&gt;
To fix this is quite important for debian, as this will be the default behaviour of ld for the next release (wheezy). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A proposed patch for 1.8.5 is added to this bugreport (and needs to be ported to 2.x) (which I can do after having a look on review.whamcloud.com to see how this will work).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Greetings&lt;br/&gt;
Patrick&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>This bug can be reproduced with 1.8.5 on debian unstable</environment>
